import Scott1980.Neighborhood.Proposition710
import Scott1980.Neighborhood.Definition72
import Scott1980.Neighborhood.FunctionSpace

/-!
# Exercise 7.19 (Scott 1981, PRG-19, ¬ß7) ‚ÄĒ `D ‚Ü¶ ‚ĄôD` is a functor

> **EXERCISE 7.19.** Prove that `D ‚Ü¶ ‚ĄôD` is a functor by defining for each `f : D ‚Üí E` a mapping
> `‚Ąôf : ‚ĄôD ‚Üí ‚ĄôE` by the formula
> `‚čÉ_{i<n} ‚ÜďXŠĶĘ  ‚Ąôf  ‚čÉ_{j<m} ‚ÜďY‚Īľ   iff   ‚ąÄ i<n ‚ąÉ j<m. XŠĶĘ f Y‚Īľ`.
> Be sure to check that `‚Ąôf` is approximable and that `‚Ąô` preserves identity maps and composition.
> If `f` is computable, is `‚Ąôf`? Is there a combinator `őĽf. ‚Ąôf`? What is `‚Ąôf({x, y}) = ??`

## The mapping `‚Ąôf`

Scott's formula refers to a *representation* `A = ‚čÉ_{i<n} ‚ÜďXŠĶĘ`, which is not unique. We give the
**representation-independent** relation

`(‚Ąôf).rel A B  :=  A ‚ąą ‚ĄôD ‚ąß B ‚ąą ‚ĄôE ‚ąß ‚ąÄ X ‚ąą A, ‚ąÉ Y ‚ąą B, X f Y`   (`PFmap`),

and prove it agrees with Scott's display on any generators (`PFmap_rel_fin`): for finite lists
`L‚āĀ ‚äÜ ūĚíü`, `L‚āā ‚äÜ ‚Ąį`,

`(‚Ąôf).rel (‚čÉ_{X‚ąąL‚āĀ} ‚ÜďX) (‚čÉ_{Y‚ąąL‚āā} ‚ÜďY)  ‚ÜĒ  ‚ąÄ X ‚ąą L‚āĀ, ‚ąÉ Y ‚ąą L‚āā, X f Y`.

The two readings coincide because every member `X ‚ąą A` lies below a generator `XŠĶĘ` and `f` is
monotone (`mono`), and conversely each generator is itself a member. Approximability (`PFmap`) uses:
`master_rel` from `f.master_rel`; `inter_right` from `f.inter_right` together with the fact that the
power domain is *downward closed* (`PDmem_down`) so the witness `Y ‚ą© Y'` lands back in `B ‚ą© B'`;
`mono` is immediate (the body only quantifies over set membership).

## Functoriality

* `PFmap_idMap` ‚ÄĒ `‚Ąô(I_D) = I_{‚ĄôD}` (the body `‚ąÄ X ‚ąą A, ‚ąÉ Y ‚ąą B, X ‚äÜ Y` collapses to `A ‚äÜ B` by
  downward closure).
* `PFmap_comp` ‚ÄĒ `‚Ąô(g ‚ąė f) = ‚Ąôg ‚ąė ‚Ąôf`. The non-trivial direction builds the intermediate
  `‚ĄôE`-neighbourhood `B = ‚čÉ_{Y‚ąąM} ‚ÜďY` from a list `M` of witnesses gathered along the generators of
  `A` by a **choice-free** list recursion (`comp_witness`: `obtain`-ing each existential witness in a
  `Prop` goal needs no choice).

## Discussion (Scott's three questions)

* **If `f` is computable, is `‚Ąôf`?** *Yes* (`PFmap_isComputable` / `PFmap_isComputable_Ypd`). Over the
  canonical presentations of Proposition 7.10 (`PDPresentation`, codes = finite lists of `ūĚíü`-indices),
  the relation reduces (`PFmap_rel_Ypd_iff`) to
  `‚ąÄ a ‚ąą dl c, ‚ąÉ b ‚ąą dl d, X‚āź f Y_b`, a bounded `‚ąÄ`/`‚ąÉ` over the r.e. relation `X‚āź f Y_b`; r.e.-ness
  is preserved by bounded `‚ąÉ` (`bExists_decodeList_re`) and bounded `‚ąÄ` with a parameter
  (`REPred.forall_mem_decodeList‚āā`). So `‚Ąôf` is computable whenever `f` is.
* **Is there a combinator `őĽf. ‚Ąôf`?** *Yes* ‚ÄĒ and built in full: **`PFmapComb`** is a genuine
  `ApproximableMap (funSpace V W) (funSpace V.PowerDomain W.PowerDomain)`, i.e. an element of
  `(D ‚Üí E) ‚Üí (‚ĄôD ‚Üí ‚ĄôE)` in Scott's sense (Theorem 3.10's `funSpace`). Its relation is the flat
  Smyth-style lift `(ő¶, ő®) ‚Ü¶ mem ő¶ ‚ąß mem ő® ‚ąß ‚ąÄ f ‚ąą ő¶, ‚Ąôf ‚ąą ő®` (exactly the recipe of Exercise 7.16's
  `curryComb`/Exercise 7.21's `papplyEval`, one level up). **Faithfulness**
  (`PFmapComb_toElementMap`) confirms it *really is* `őĽf. ‚Ąôf`: under the function-space
  correspondence `funSpaceEquiv` (Thm 3.10, `toFilter`/`toApproxMap`),
  `(PFmapComb).toElementMap (toFilter f) = toFilter (PFmap f)` for **every** `f : D ‚Üí E` ‚ÄĒ not just
  finite/principal ones. The non-trivial direction gathers, for an arbitrary target neighbourhood
  `ő® = ‚čā‚Īľ [A‚Īľ, B‚Īľ]`, a single finite witness list `M` of `D√óE`-pairs (`exists_stepFun_forall_PFmap_rel`,
  built by the choice-free two-level list recursion `gather_witnesses` + outer induction) such that
  *every* `g` agreeing with `f` on `M` again has `‚Ąôg ‚ąą ő®` ‚ÄĒ precisely the continuity of `f ‚Ü¶ ‚Ąôf`
  unwound to finite data, in the same spirit as Theorem 7.4 / Exercise 7.21's combinators.
* **What is `‚Ąôf({x, y})`?** The finite element `{x, y} ‚ąą |‚ĄôD|` is the principal element of the
  generator `‚ÜďX ‚ą™ ‚ÜďX'` (with `x = ‚ÜĎX`, `y = ‚ÜĎX'`); by `PFmap_rel_fin` its image under `‚Ąôf` is
  generated by `‚Üď(f x) ‚ą™ ‚Üď(f x')`, i.e. `‚Ąôf({x, y}) = {f x, f x'}` ‚ÄĒ `‚Ąôf` is the *image* operation.

Axiom audit: every declaration carries `Classical.choice`, but only at the `Prop` level and only
*inherited* from the power domain itself: `‚ĄôūĚíü`'s closure under intersection (Proposition 7.10's
`PDmem_upSet_inter`) decides neighbourhood membership in an arbitrary system by `by_cases`, which is
genuinely undecidable at this generality. The new content of this file (the relation `PFmap`, the
display formula, both functor laws, and the r.e. reductions) adds **no further** use of choice; the
closure layer of `Recursive.lean` is choice-free, so `PFmap_isComputable*` add only the axioms of the
input `hf` on top of the power-domain's inherited `Classical.choice`.
-/

namespace Scott1980.Neighborhood

open NeighborhoodSystem Domain.Recursive ApproximableMap

variable {őĪ ő≤ ő≥ : Type*}

namespace NeighborhoodSystem

variable (V : NeighborhoodSystem őĪ)

/-- **Every member of a `‚ĄôūĚíü`-neighbourhood is a `ūĚíü`-neighbourhood.** -/
theorem PDmem_mem {A : Set (Set őĪ)} (hA : V.PDmem A) {X : Set őĪ} (hX : X ‚ąą A) : V.mem X := by
  obtain ‚ü®L, hL, rfl‚ü© := hA
  obtain ‚ü®X', _, hXmem, _‚ü© := (V.mem_PDunion).mp hX
  exact hXmem

/-- **`‚ĄôūĚíü`-neighbourhoods are downward closed.** If `Z ‚ąą A` and `X ‚äÜ Z` with `X ‚ąą ūĚíü`, then `X ‚ąą A`
(each `A = ‚čÉ ‚ÜďXŠĶĘ` is a union of down-sets). -/
theorem PDmem_down {A : Set (Set őĪ)} (hA : V.PDmem A) {Z X : Set őĪ}
    (hZ : Z ‚ąą A) (hXZ : X ‚äÜ Z) (hX : V.mem X) : X ‚ąą A := by
  obtain ‚ü®L, hL, rfl‚ü© := hA
  obtain ‚ü®X', hX', _, hZsub‚ü© := (V.mem_PDunion).mp hZ
  exact (V.mem_PDunion).mpr ‚ü®X', hX', hX, hXZ.trans hZsub‚ü©

end NeighborhoodSystem

variable {V : NeighborhoodSystem őĪ} {W : NeighborhoodSystem ő≤} {U : NeighborhoodSystem ő≥}

/-- **Exercise 7.19 (Scott 1981, PRG-19) ‚ÄĒ the functorial action `‚Ąôf : ‚ĄôD ‚Üí ‚ĄôE`.** Given an
approximable map `f : D ‚Üí E`, the relation between `‚ĄôD`- and `‚ĄôE`-neighbourhoods is "every member of
the source is `f`-related to some member of the target". This is the representation-independent form
of Scott's displayed `‚ąÄ i < n ‚ąÉ j < m. XŠĶĘ f Y‚Īľ` (see `PFmap_rel_fin`). -/
def PFmap (f : ApproximableMap V W) : ApproximableMap V.PowerDomain W.PowerDomain where
  rel A B := V.PDmem A ‚ąß W.PDmem B ‚ąß ‚ąÄ X ‚ąą A, ‚ąÉ Y ‚ąą B, f.rel X Y
  rel_dom h := h.1
  rel_cod h := h.2.1
  master_rel := by
    refine ‚ü®V.PDmem_master, W.PDmem_master, ?_‚ü©
    rintro X ‚ü®hXmem, hXsub‚ü©
    exact ‚ü®W.master, ‚ü®W.master_mem, subset_rfl‚ü©,
      f.mono f.master_rel hXsub subset_rfl hXmem W.master_mem‚ü©
  inter_right := by
    rintro A B B' ‚ü®hA, hB, hbody‚ü© ‚ü®-, hB', hbody'‚ü©
    refine ‚ü®hA, W.PDmem_inter hB hB', ?_‚ü©
    intro X hX
    obtain ‚ü®Y, hYB, hrel‚ü© := hbody X hX
    obtain ‚ü®Y', hY'B', hrel'‚ü© := hbody' X hX
    have hinmem : W.mem (Y ‚ą© Y') := f.rel_cod (f.inter_right hrel hrel')
    exact ‚ü®Y ‚ą© Y', Set.mem_inter
      (W.PDmem_down hB hYB Set.inter_subset_left hinmem)
      (W.PDmem_down hB' hY'B' Set.inter_subset_right hinmem),
      f.inter_right hrel hrel'‚ü©
  mono := by
    rintro A A' B B' ‚ü®_, _, hbody‚ü© hA'A hBB' hA' hB'
    refine ‚ü®hA', hB', ?_‚ü©
    intro X hX
    obtain ‚ü®Y, hYB, hrel‚ü© := hbody X (hA'A hX)
    exact ‚ü®Y, hBB' hYB, hrel‚ü©

@[simp] theorem PFmap_rel {f : ApproximableMap V W} {A : Set (Set őĪ)} {B : Set (Set ő≤)} :
    (PFmap f).rel A B ‚ÜĒ V.PDmem A ‚ąß W.PDmem B ‚ąß ‚ąÄ X ‚ąą A, ‚ąÉ Y ‚ąą B, f.rel X Y := Iff.rfl

/-- **Exercise 7.19 ‚ÄĒ Scott's displayed formula.** On generators (finite lists of down-sets)
`(‚Ąôf).rel (‚čÉ_{X‚ąąL‚āĀ} ‚ÜďX) (‚čÉ_{Y‚ąąL‚āā} ‚ÜďY) ‚ÜĒ ‚ąÄ X ‚ąą L‚āĀ, ‚ąÉ Y ‚ąą L‚āā, X f Y`, exactly Scott's
`‚ąÄ i < n ‚ąÉ j < m. XŠĶĘ f Y‚Īľ`. (`‚Üí` reads off the generators `XŠĶĘ`; `‚Üź` extends to all members by `mono`
and downward closure of the target.) -/
theorem PFmap_rel_fin (f : ApproximableMap V W) {L‚āĀ : List (Set őĪ)} {L‚āā : List (Set ő≤)}
    (hL‚āĀ : ‚ąÄ X ‚ąą L‚āĀ, V.mem X) (hL‚āā : ‚ąÄ Y ‚ąą L‚āā, W.mem Y) :
    (PFmap f).rel (‚čÉ X ‚ąą L‚āĀ, V.upSet X) (‚čÉ Y ‚ąą L‚āā, W.upSet Y)
      ‚ÜĒ ‚ąÄ X ‚ąą L‚āĀ, ‚ąÉ Y ‚ąą L‚āā, f.rel X Y := by
  constructor
  ¬∑ rintro ‚ü®-, -, hbody‚ü© X hX
    have hXin : X ‚ąą ‚čÉ X' ‚ąą L‚āĀ, V.upSet X' :=
      (V.mem_PDunion).mpr ‚ü®X, hX, hL‚āĀ X hX, subset_rfl‚ü©
    obtain ‚ü®Z, hZin, hrel‚ü© := hbody X hXin
    obtain ‚ü®Y, hY, hZmem, hZsub‚ü© := (W.mem_PDunion).mp hZin
    exact ‚ü®Y, hY, f.mono hrel subset_rfl hZsub (hL‚āĀ X hX) (hL‚āā Y hY)‚ü©
  ¬∑ intro hgen
    refine ‚ü®‚ü®L‚āĀ, hL‚āĀ, rfl‚ü©, ‚ü®L‚āā, hL‚āā, rfl‚ü©, ?_‚ü©
    rintro Z hZin
    obtain ‚ü®X, hX, hZmem, hZsub‚ü© := (V.mem_PDunion).mp hZin
    obtain ‚ü®Y, hY, hrel‚ü© := hgen X hX
    exact ‚ü®Y, (W.mem_PDunion).mpr ‚ü®Y, hY, hL‚āā Y hY, subset_rfl‚ü©,
      f.mono hrel hZsub subset_rfl hZmem (hL‚āā Y hY)‚ü©

/-! ### Functoriality: `‚Ąô` preserves identities and composition. -/

/-- **Exercise 7.19 ‚ÄĒ `‚Ąô` preserves identity maps.** `‚Ąô(I_D) = I_{‚ĄôD}`. The body
`‚ąÄ X ‚ąą A, ‚ąÉ Y ‚ąą B, X ‚äÜ Y` is equivalent to `A ‚äÜ B` by downward closure of `B`. -/
theorem PFmap_idMap (V : NeighborhoodSystem őĪ) : PFmap (idMap V) = idMap V.PowerDomain := by
  apply ApproximableMap.ext
  intro A B
  simp only [PFmap_rel, idMap_rel, PowerDomain_mem]
  constructor
  ¬∑ rintro ‚ü®hA, hB, hbody‚ü©
    refine ‚ü®hA, hB, ?_‚ü©
    intro X hX
    obtain ‚ü®Y, hYB, hXmem, _, hXY‚ü© := hbody X hX
    exact V.PDmem_down hB hYB hXY hXmem
  ¬∑ rintro ‚ü®hA, hB, hsub‚ü©
    refine ‚ü®hA, hB, ?_‚ü©
    intro X hX
    exact ‚ü®X, hsub hX, V.PDmem_mem hA hX, V.PDmem_mem hA hX, subset_rfl‚ü©

/-- Choice-free gathering of composition witnesses along the generators of the source: from a list
`L` of `ūĚíü`-neighbourhoods each admitting a `(g‚ąėf)`-witness into `C`, build a single list `M` of
`‚Ąį`-neighbourhoods covering every `X ‚ąą L` from the `f`-side and covered into `C` from the `g`-side.
Proved by list recursion `obtain`-ing the witnesses (no choice in a `Prop` goal). -/
theorem comp_witness (f : ApproximableMap V W) (g : ApproximableMap W U) (C : Set (Set ő≥)) :
    ‚ąÄ (L : List (Set őĪ)), (‚ąÄ X ‚ąą L, V.mem X) ‚Üí
      (‚ąÄ X ‚ąą L, ‚ąÉ Z, Z ‚ąą C ‚ąß ‚ąÉ Y, f.rel X Y ‚ąß g.rel Y Z) ‚Üí
      ‚ąÉ M : List (Set ő≤), (‚ąÄ Y ‚ąą M, W.mem Y) ‚ąß
        (‚ąÄ X ‚ąą L, ‚ąÉ Y ‚ąą M, f.rel X Y) ‚ąß (‚ąÄ Y ‚ąą M, ‚ąÉ Z ‚ąą C, g.rel Y Z) := by
  intro L
  induction L with
  | nil =>
    intro _ _
    refine ‚ü®[], ?_, ?_, ?_‚ü©
    ¬∑ intro Y hY; cases hY
    ¬∑ intro X hX; cases hX
    ¬∑ intro Y hY; cases hY
  | cons X L ih =>
    intro hL hpre
    obtain ‚ü®Zx, hZxC, Yx, hfx, hgx‚ü© := hpre X (List.mem_cons.mpr (Or.inl rfl))
    obtain ‚ü®M, hMmem, hfM, hgM‚ü© :=
      ih (fun X' hX' => hL X' (List.mem_cons.mpr (Or.inr hX')))
         (fun X' hX' => hpre X' (List.mem_cons.mpr (Or.inr hX')))
    refine ‚ü®Yx :: M, ?_, ?_, ?_‚ü©
    ¬∑ intro Y hY
      rcases List.mem_cons.mp hY with rfl | hY'
      ¬∑ exact f.rel_cod hfx
      ¬∑ exact hMmem Y hY'
    ¬∑ intro X' hX'
      rcases List.mem_cons.mp hX' with rfl | hX''
      ¬∑ exact ‚ü®Yx, List.mem_cons.mpr (Or.inl rfl), hfx‚ü©
      ¬∑ obtain ‚ü®Y, hYM, hrel‚ü© := hfM X' hX''
        exact ‚ü®Y, List.mem_cons.mpr (Or.inr hYM), hrel‚ü©
    ¬∑ intro Y hY
      rcases List.mem_cons.mp hY with rfl | hY'
      ¬∑ exact ‚ü®Zx, hZxC, hgx‚ü©
      ¬∑ exact hgM Y hY'

/-- **Exercise 7.19 ‚ÄĒ `‚Ąô` preserves composition.** `‚Ąô(g ‚ąė f) = ‚Ąôg ‚ąė ‚Ąôf`. The forward direction
constructs the intermediate `‚ĄôE`-neighbourhood from `comp_witness`; the backward direction merely
threads the existential witnesses. -/
theorem PFmap_comp (g : ApproximableMap W U) (f : ApproximableMap V W) :
    PFmap (g.comp f) = (PFmap g).comp (PFmap f) := by
  apply ApproximableMap.ext
  intro A C
  simp only [PFmap_rel, comp_rel]
  constructor
  ¬∑ rintro ‚ü®hA, hC, hbody‚ü©
    obtain ‚ü®L, hL, rfl‚ü© := hA
    have hpre : ‚ąÄ X ‚ąą L, ‚ąÉ Z, Z ‚ąą C ‚ąß ‚ąÉ Y, f.rel X Y ‚ąß g.rel Y Z := by
      intro X hX
      obtain ‚ü®Z, hZC, Y, hfXY, hgYZ‚ü© :=
        hbody X ((V.mem_PDunion).mpr ‚ü®X, hX, hL X hX, subset_rfl‚ü©)
      exact ‚ü®Z, hZC, Y, hfXY, hgYZ‚ü©
    obtain ‚ü®M, hMmem, hfL, hgM‚ü© := comp_witness f g C L hL hpre
    refine ‚ü®‚čÉ Y ‚ąą M, W.upSet Y,
      ‚ü®‚ü®L, hL, rfl‚ü©, ‚ü®M, hMmem, rfl‚ü©, ?_‚ü©, ‚ü®M, hMmem, rfl‚ü©, hC, ?_‚ü©
    ¬∑ intro X hX
      obtain ‚ü®X', hX', hXmem, hXsub‚ü© := (V.mem_PDunion).mp hX
      obtain ‚ü®Y, hYM, hrel‚ü© := hfL X' hX'
      exact ‚ü®Y, (W.mem_PDunion).mpr ‚ü®Y, hYM, hMmem Y hYM, subset_rfl‚ü©,
        f.mono hrel hXsub subset_rfl hXmem (hMmem Y hYM)‚ü©
    ¬∑ intro Y hY
      obtain ‚ü®Y', hY', hYmem, hYsub‚ü© := (W.mem_PDunion).mp hY
      obtain ‚ü®Z, hZC, hrel‚ü© := hgM Y' hY'
      exact ‚ü®Z, hZC, g.mono hrel hYsub subset_rfl hYmem (g.rel_cod hrel)‚ü©
  ¬∑ rintro ‚ü®B, ‚ü®hA, hB, hfAB‚ü©, _, hC, hgBC‚ü©
    refine ‚ü®hA, hC, ?_‚ü©
    intro X hX
    obtain ‚ü®Y, hYB, hfXY‚ü© := hfAB X hX
    obtain ‚ü®Z, hZC, hgYZ‚ü© := hgBC Y hYB
    exact ‚ü®Z, hZC, Y, hfXY, hgYZ‚ü©

/-! ### Computability: if `f` is computable then so is `‚Ąôf` (Scott's first question). -/

/-- **Bounded `‚ąÉ` over a coded list preserves recursive enumerability.** If `R` is r.e. then so is
`fun d a => ‚ąÉ b ‚ąą decodeList d, R a b`: project out `b` (`REPred.proj`) over the conjunction of the
*recursively decidable* membership `b ‚ąą decodeList d` with the r.e. body `R a b`. -/
theorem bExists_decodeList_re {R : ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąē ‚Üí Prop} (hR : REPred‚āā R) :
    REPred‚āā (fun d a => ‚ąÉ b ‚ąą decodeList d, R a b) := by
  have hmem : RecDecidable‚āā (fun d b => b ‚ąą decodeList d) := by
    have heq : RecDecidable‚āā (fun e b => e = b) :=
      RecDecidable.natEq Nat.Primrec.left Nat.Primrec.right
    have hbase : RecDecidable‚āā (fun d b => ‚ąÉ e ‚ąą decodeList d, e = b) := heq.bExistsList
    refine RecDecidable.of_iff (fun t => ?_) hbase
    constructor
    ¬∑ intro h; exact ‚ü®_, h, rfl‚ü©
    ¬∑ rintro ‚ü®e, he, rfl‚ü©; exact he
  have hpart1 : REPred (fun w : ‚Ąē => w.unpair.1 ‚ąą decodeList w.unpair.2.unpair.1) := by
    have hg : Nat.Primrec (fun w : ‚Ąē => Nat.pair w.unpair.2.unpair.1 w.unpair.1) :=
      (Nat.Primrec.left.comp Nat.Primrec.right).pair Nat.Primrec.left
    refine RecDecidable.re (RecDecidable.of_iff (fun w => ?_) (hmem.comp hg))
    simp only [unpair_pair_fst, unpair_pair_snd]
  have hpart2 : REPred (fun w : ‚Ąē => R w.unpair.2.unpair.2 w.unpair.1) := by
    have hg : Nat.Primrec (fun w : ‚Ąē => Nat.pair w.unpair.2.unpair.2 w.unpair.1) :=
      (Nat.Primrec.right.comp Nat.Primrec.right).pair Nat.Primrec.left
    refine REPred.of_iff (fun w => ?_) (REPred.comp hR hg)
    simp only [unpair_pair_fst, unpair_pair_snd]
  refine REPred.of_iff (fun s => ?_) (hpart1.and hpart2).proj
  simp only [unpair_pair_fst, unpair_pair_snd]

/-- **Exercise 7.19 ‚ÄĒ the relation of `‚Ąôf` at the level of `‚ĄôūĚíü`-codes.** Over the canonical
presentations of Proposition 7.10, `(‚Ąôf).rel (Y_c) (Y_d) ‚ÜĒ ‚ąÄ a ‚ąą dl c, ‚ąÉ b ‚ąą dl d, X‚āź f Y_b`. -/
theorem PFmap_rel_Ypd_iff (P : ComputablePresentation V) (Q : ComputablePresentation W)
    (f : ApproximableMap V W) {c d : ‚Ąē} :
    (PFmap f).rel (V.Ypd P c) (W.Ypd Q d) ‚ÜĒ
      ‚ąÄ a ‚ąą decodeList c, ‚ąÉ b ‚ąą decodeList d, f.rel (P.X a) (Q.X b) := by
  constructor
  ¬∑ rintro ‚ü®-, -, hbody‚ü© a ha
    have hXin : P.X a ‚ąą V.Ypd P c := (V.mem_Ypd P).mpr ‚ü®a, ha, P.mem_X a, subset_rfl‚ü©
    obtain ‚ü®Y, hYin, hrel‚ü© := hbody (P.X a) hXin
    obtain ‚ü®b, hb, hYmem, hYsub‚ü© := (W.mem_Ypd Q).mp hYin
    exact ‚ü®b, hb, f.mono hrel subset_rfl hYsub (P.mem_X a) (Q.mem_X b)‚ü©
  ¬∑ intro hgen
    refine ‚ü®V.Ypd_isPDmem P c, W.Ypd_isPDmem Q d, ?_‚ü©
    rintro X hXin
    obtain ‚ü®a, ha, hXmem, hXsub‚ü© := (V.mem_Ypd P).mp hXin
    obtain ‚ü®b, hb, hrel‚ü© := hgen a ha
    exact ‚ü®Q.X b, (W.mem_Ypd Q).mpr ‚ü®b, hb, Q.mem_X b, subset_rfl‚ü©,
      f.mono hrel hXsub subset_rfl hXmem (Q.mem_X b)‚ü©

/-- **Exercise 7.19 (Scott's first question) ‚ÄĒ `‚Ąôf` is computable when `f` is.** Stated at the level
of the `‚ĄôūĚíü`-codes of Proposition 7.10 (`Y_c = ‚čÉ_{a‚ąądl c} ‚ÜďX‚āź`): the relation `(‚Ąôf).rel (Y_c) (Y_d)`
is recursively enumerable in `(c, d)`. -/
theorem PFmap_isComputable_Ypd (P : ComputablePresentation V) (Q : ComputablePresentation W)
    {f : ApproximableMap V W} (hf : IsComputableMap P Q f) :
    REPred‚āā (fun c d => (PFmap f).rel (V.Ypd P c) (W.Ypd Q d)) := by
  have hR : REPred‚āā (fun a b => f.rel (P.X a) (Q.X b)) := hf
  have hInner : REPred‚āā (fun d a => ‚ąÉ b ‚ąą decodeList d, f.rel (P.X a) (Q.X b)) :=
    bExists_decodeList_re hR
  have hForall := REPred.forall_mem_decodeList‚āā hInner
  have hswap : Nat.Primrec (fun s : ‚Ąē => Nat.pair s.unpair.2 s.unpair.1) :=
    Nat.Primrec.right.pair Nat.Primrec.left
  refine REPred.of_iff (fun s => ?_) (hForall.comp hswap)
  simp only [unpair_pair_fst, unpair_pair_snd]
  exact PFmap_rel_Ypd_iff P Q f

/-- **Exercise 7.19 (Scott's first question), packaged.** `‚Ąôf` is a computable map between the
canonical effective presentations `‚ĄôūĚíü`, `‚Ąô‚Ąį` (Proposition 7.10) whenever `f` is computable. -/
theorem PFmap_isComputable (P : ComputablePresentation V) (Q : ComputablePresentation W)
    (consV : ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąē) (hconsVp : Nat.Primrec consV)
    (hconsVs : ‚ąÄ a b, consV (Nat.pair a b) = 1 ‚ÜĒ ‚ąÉ k, P.X k ‚äÜ P.X a ‚ą© P.X b)
    (consW : ‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąē) (hconsWp : Nat.Primrec consW)
    (hconsWs : ‚ąÄ a b, consW (Nat.pair a b) = 1 ‚ÜĒ ‚ąÉ k, Q.X k ‚äÜ Q.X a ‚ą© Q.X b)
    {f : ApproximableMap V W} (hf : IsComputableMap P Q f) :
    IsComputableMap (V.PDPresentation P consV hconsVp hconsVs)
      (W.PDPresentation Q consW hconsWp hconsWs) (PFmap f) := by
  exact PFmap_isComputable_Ypd P Q hf

/-! ### The combinator `őĽf. ‚Ąôf` (Scott's second question). -/

/-- **Choice-free witness gathering (single list).** From `‚ąÄ X ‚ąą L‚āĀ, ‚ąÉ Y ‚ąą L‚āā, f.rel X Y`, build one
list `M` of `(X, Y)` pairs, each drawn from `L‚āĀ √ó L‚āā` and `f`-related, that *covers* `L‚āĀ`: every
`X ‚ąą L‚āĀ` has a matching `Y` with `(X, Y) ‚ąą M`. (The one-map analogue of `comp_witness`.) -/
theorem gather_witnesses (f : ApproximableMap V W) :
    ‚ąÄ (L‚āĀ : List (Set őĪ)) (L‚āā : List (Set ő≤)), (‚ąÄ X ‚ąą L‚āĀ, ‚ąÉ Y ‚ąą L‚āā, f.rel X Y) ‚Üí
      ‚ąÉ M : List (Set őĪ √ó Set ő≤), (‚ąÄ p ‚ąą M, p.1 ‚ąą L‚āĀ ‚ąß p.2 ‚ąą L‚āā ‚ąß f.rel p.1 p.2) ‚ąß
        ‚ąÄ X ‚ąą L‚āĀ, ‚ąÉ Y ‚ąą L‚āā, (X, Y) ‚ąą M := by
  intro L‚āĀ
  induction L‚āĀ with
  | nil => intro L‚āā _; exact ‚ü®[], by simp, by simp‚ü©
  | cons X L‚āĀ ih =>
    intro L‚āā h
    obtain ‚ü®Y, hY, hrel‚ü© := h X (List.mem_cons.mpr (Or.inl rfl))
    obtain ‚ü®M, hMprop, hMwit‚ü© := ih L‚āā (fun X' hX' => h X' (List.mem_cons.mpr (Or.inr hX')))
    refine ‚ü®(X, Y) :: M, ?_, ?_‚ü©
    ¬∑ rintro p hp
      rcases List.mem_cons.mp hp with rfl | hp'
      ¬∑ exact ‚ü®List.mem_cons.mpr (Or.inl rfl), hY, hrel‚ü©
      ¬∑ obtain ‚ü®hX1, hY1, hrel1‚ü© := hMprop p hp'
        exact ‚ü®List.mem_cons.mpr (Or.inr hX1), hY1, hrel1‚ü©
    ¬∑ intro X' hX'
      rcases List.mem_cons.mp hX' with rfl | hX''
      ¬∑ exact ‚ü®Y, hY, List.mem_cons.mpr (Or.inl rfl)‚ü©
      ¬∑ obtain ‚ü®Y', hY', hmem‚ü© := hMwit X' hX''
        exact ‚ü®Y', hY', List.mem_cons.mpr (Or.inr hmem)‚ü©

/-- **Choice-free witness gathering (list of step constraints).** From a finite list `L` of
`‚ĄôD √ó ‚ĄôE`-neighbourhood pairs `(A, B)`, each satisfied by `‚Ąôf` (`(‚Ąôf).rel A B`), build a *single*
finite list `M` of `D √ó E`-pairs, `f`-related and covering every generator of every `A` in `L`, such
that *any* `g` agreeing with `f` on `M` again satisfies `(‚Ąôg).rel A B` for every `(A, B) ‚ąą L`. This is
exactly "continuity of `f ‚Ü¶ ‚Ąôf`, unwound to finite data": `M` is the finite portion of `f` that
already forces `‚Ąôf`'s membership in every step-neighbourhood of `L`. -/
theorem exists_stepFun_forall_PFmap_rel (f : ApproximableMap V W) :
    ‚ąÄ (L : List (Set (Set őĪ) √ó Set (Set ő≤))),
      (‚ąÄ p ‚ąą L, V.PDmem p.1 ‚ąß W.PDmem p.2) ‚Üí (‚ąÄ p ‚ąą L, (PFmap f).rel p.1 p.2) ‚Üí
      ‚ąÉ M : List (Set őĪ √ó Set ő≤), (‚ąÄ p ‚ąą M, V.mem p.1 ‚ąß W.mem p.2) ‚ąß
        (‚ąÄ p ‚ąą M, f.rel p.1 p.2) ‚ąß
        ‚ąÄ g : ApproximableMap V W, (‚ąÄ p ‚ąą M, g.rel p.1 p.2) ‚Üí ‚ąÄ p ‚ąą L, (PFmap g).rel p.1 p.2 := by
  intro L
  induction L with
  | nil => intro _ _; exact ‚ü®[], by simp, by simp, by simp‚ü©
  | cons p L ih =>
    intro hL hf
    obtain ‚ü®hA, hB‚ü© := hL p (List.mem_cons.mpr (Or.inl rfl))
    obtain ‚ü®L‚āĀ, hL‚āĀ, hAeq‚ü© := hA
    obtain ‚ü®L‚āā, hL‚āā, hBeq‚ü© := hB
    have hrelAB : (PFmap f).rel p.1 p.2 := hf p (List.mem_cons.mpr (Or.inl rfl))
    rw [hAeq, hBeq] at hrelAB
    have hgen := (PFmap_rel_fin f hL‚āĀ hL‚āā).mp hrelAB
    obtain ‚ü®M‚āÄ, hM‚āÄprop, hM‚āÄwit‚ü© := gather_witnesses f L‚āĀ L‚āā hgen
    obtain ‚ü®M, hMmem, hMrel, hMgen‚ü© :=
      ih (fun p' hp' => hL p' (List.mem_cons.mpr (Or.inr hp')))
         (fun p' hp' => hf p' (List.mem_cons.mpr (Or.inr hp')))
    refine ‚ü®M‚āÄ ++ M, ?_, ?_, ?_‚ü©
    ¬∑ intro q hq
      rcases List.mem_append.mp hq with hq' | hq'
      ¬∑ obtain ‚ü®hq1, hq2, _‚ü© := hM‚āÄprop q hq'
        exact ‚ü®hL‚āĀ q.1 hq1, hL‚āā q.2 hq2‚ü©
      ¬∑ exact hMmem q hq'
    ¬∑ intro q hq
      rcases List.mem_append.mp hq with hq' | hq'
      ¬∑ exact (hM‚āÄprop q hq').2.2
      ¬∑ exact hMrel q hq'
    ¬∑ intro g hg p' hp'
      rcases List.mem_cons.mp hp' with rfl | hp''
      ¬∑ rw [hAeq, hBeq]
        refine (PFmap_rel_fin g hL‚āĀ hL‚āā).mpr ?_
        intro X hX
        obtain ‚ü®Y, hY, hmem‚ü© := hM‚āÄwit X hX
        exact ‚ü®Y, hY, hg (X, Y) (List.mem_append.mpr (Or.inl hmem))‚ü©
      ¬∑ exact hMgen g (fun q hq => hg q (List.mem_append.mpr (Or.inr hq))) p' hp''

/-- **Exercise 7.19 ‚ÄĒ the combinator `őĽf. ‚Ąôf : (D ‚Üí E) ‚Üí (‚ĄôD ‚Üí ‚ĄôE)`.** The flat Smyth-style lift
`(ő¶, ő®) ‚Ü¶ mem ő¶ ‚ąß mem ő® ‚ąß ‚ąÄ f ‚ąą ő¶, ‚Ąôf ‚ąą ő®` of Exercise 7.19's functorial action, one level up on the
function spaces (`funSpace`, Theorem 3.10) ‚ÄĒ the same recipe as Exercise 7.16's `curryComb` and
Exercise 7.21's `papplyEval`. Approximability is immediate: unlike `PFmap` itself, the body is a bare
membership check with no witnesses to gather. -/
def PFmapComb (V : NeighborhoodSystem őĪ) (W : NeighborhoodSystem ő≤) :
    ApproximableMap (funSpace V W) (funSpace V.PowerDomain W.PowerDomain) where
  rel ő¶ ő® := (funSpace V W).mem ő¶ ‚ąß (funSpace V.PowerDomain W.PowerDomain).mem ő® ‚ąß
    ‚ąÄ f ‚ąą ő¶, PFmap f ‚ąą ő®
  rel_dom h := h.1
  rel_cod h := h.2.1
  master_rel :=
    ‚ü®(funSpace V W).master_mem, (funSpace V.PowerDomain W.PowerDomain).master_mem,
      fun _ _ => Set.mem_univ _‚ü©
  inter_right := by
    rintro ő¶ ő® ő®' ‚ü®hő¶, hő®, hbody‚ü© ‚ü®-, hő®', hbody'‚ü©
    obtain ‚ü®f‚āÄ, hf‚āÄ‚ü© := hő¶.2
    obtain ‚ü®‚ü®L‚āā, hL‚āā, rfl‚ü©, -‚ü© := hő®
    obtain ‚ü®‚ü®L‚āā', hL‚āā', rfl‚ü©, -‚ü© := hő®'
    refine ‚ü®hő¶, ‚ü®‚ü®L‚āā ++ L‚āā', ?_, (stepFun_append _ _).symm‚ü©,
        ‚ü®PFmap f‚āÄ, Set.mem_inter (hbody f‚āÄ hf‚āÄ) (hbody' f‚āÄ hf‚āÄ)‚ü©‚ü©,
      fun f hf => Set.mem_inter (hbody f hf) (hbody' f hf)‚ü©
    intro q hq
    rcases List.mem_append.mp hq with hq' | hq'
    ¬∑ exact hL‚āā q hq'
    ¬∑ exact hL‚āā' q hq'
  mono := by
    rintro ő¶ ő¶' ő® ő®' ‚ü®_, _, hbody‚ü© hő¶'ő¶ hő®ő®' hő¶' hő®'
    exact ‚ü®hő¶', hő®', fun f hf => hő®ő®' (hbody f (hő¶'ő¶ hf))‚ü©

@[simp] theorem PFmapComb_rel {ő¶ : Set (ApproximableMap V W)}
    {ő® : Set (ApproximableMap V.PowerDomain W.PowerDomain)} :
    (PFmapComb V W).rel ő¶ ő® ‚ÜĒ
      (funSpace V W).mem ő¶ ‚ąß (funSpace V.PowerDomain W.PowerDomain).mem ő® ‚ąß
        ‚ąÄ f ‚ąą ő¶, PFmap f ‚ąą ő® := Iff.rfl

/-- **Exercise 7.19 ‚ÄĒ faithfulness of `PFmapComb`.** Under the function-space correspondence of
Theorem 3.10 (`toFilter f` is the point of `(D ‚Üí E)` fixed by `f`), `PFmapComb` really does send
`f` to `‚Ąôf`, at **every** `f` ‚ÄĒ not merely the finite/principal points. The forward direction is
immediate; the backward direction is where the work is: given `‚Ąôf ‚ąą ő®`, `exists_stepFun_forall_PFmap_rel`
manufactures a finite neighbourhood `stepFun M ‚ąč f` all of whose members `g` already satisfy `‚Ąôg ‚ąą ő®`,
i.e. `ő®` is reached from a genuine (finite) neighbourhood of `f`, exactly as continuity demands. -/
theorem PFmapComb_toElementMap (f : ApproximableMap V W) :
    (PFmapComb V W).toElementMap (toFilter f) = toFilter (PFmap f) := by
  apply Element.ext
  intro ő®
  simp only [mem_toElementMap, mem_toFilter, PFmapComb_rel]
  constructor
  ¬∑ rintro ‚ü®ő¶, ‚ü®_, hő¶f‚ü©, _, hő®mem, hbody‚ü©
    exact ‚ü®hő®mem, hbody f hő¶f‚ü©
  ¬∑ rintro ‚ü®hő®mem, hfő®‚ü©
    obtain ‚ü®‚ü®L‚āā, hL‚āā, rfl‚ü©, -‚ü© := hő®mem
    obtain ‚ü®M, hMmem, hMrel, hMgen‚ü© :=
      exists_stepFun_forall_PFmap_rel f L‚āā hL‚āā (mem_stepFun.mp hfő®)
    have hő¶mem : (funSpace V W).mem (stepFun M) := ‚ü®‚ü®M, hMmem, rfl‚ü©, f, mem_stepFun.mpr hMrel‚ü©
    have hő®mem' : (funSpace V.PowerDomain W.PowerDomain).mem (stepFun L‚āā) :=
      ‚ü®‚ü®L‚āā, hL‚āā, rfl‚ü©, PFmap f, hfő®‚ü©
    exact ‚ü®stepFun M, ‚ü®hő¶mem, mem_stepFun.mpr hMrel‚ü©, hő¶mem, hő®mem',
      fun g hg => mem_stepFun.mpr (hMgen g (mem_stepFun.mp hg))‚ü©

